  "why": "The paper applies mutations directly to raw image pixel values (e.g., adding Gaussian or random noise, row/column mutations, and shifts), which operates in the same numerical space as serialized images and is therefore less sensitive to the serialization-reproducibility problem than mutations in latent/normalized spaces. However, the paper does not explicitly state any enforcement of input-format constraints (e.g., clipping to [0,255] or rounding to integer pixel values) or describe how mutated floating-point pixel values are handled before encoding/serialization. Because mutations are performed on raw pixels but the paper gives no explicit clipping/rounding/serialization handling, the method matches the metric's 'Medium' category: direct raw-value mutation without explicit enforcement of format constraints.",
